      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What is Khadi?</h2>
        <p>
          Khadi is a hand-spun and handwoven natural fiber cloth, originating
          from India. Known for its eco-friendly production process, Khadi
          represents simplicity, sustainability, and self-reliance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Importance of Khadi</h2>
        <p>
          Khadi is more than just a fabric; it is a symbol of India's freedom
          struggle and Gandhian principles. Its production supports rural
          artisans, reduces carbon footprint, and promotes sustainable fashion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>History of Khadi</h2>
        <p>
          Khadi became a movement during India’s independence struggle,
          spearheaded by Mahatma Gandhi. It encouraged self-reliance and
          boycotting foreign goods, becoming a powerful tool for economic and
          social transformation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Why Wear Khadi?</h2>
        <p>
          Wearing Khadi is a statement of support for sustainable practices and
          rural livelihoods. It is breathable, skin-friendly, and versatile,
          making it ideal for all seasons and occasions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>How is Khadi Made?</h2>
        <p>
          Khadi is crafted through a meticulous process of spinning cotton,
          silk, or wool into yarn using a charkha (spinning wheel), followed by
          weaving it into fabric on a handloom. This process is entirely manual,
          requiring skill and patience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Benefits of Khadi</h2>
        <p>
          Khadi is biodegradable, eco-friendly, and hypoallergenic. It supports
          local artisans, reduces energy consumption, and offers unique textures
          and patterns that machine-made fabrics cannot replicate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          At KhadiBV, we aim to revive the heritage of Khadi by making it
          accessible and appealing to modern consumers. We strive to empower
          artisans, promote sustainable fashion, and spread awareness about the
          importance of eco-friendly practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>FAQs</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Q: Is Khadi only made in India?</strong><br />A: Yes,
          authentic Khadi is handwoven in India by skilled artisans.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Q: Can Khadi be worn in all seasons?</strong><br />A:
          Absolutely! Khadi’s breathable nature makes it suitable for summer,
          while its insulating properties keep you warm in winter.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Q: How do I care for Khadi garments?</strong><br />A: Handwash
          your Khadi clothes in cold water with mild detergent and dry them in
          the shade to maintain their texture and longevity.
        </p>
